    - m_Type: 1
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Instructions
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "<b>1.</b>  In the <b>Hierarchy</b> window, select the <b>Camera</b>
          GameObject. \n\n<b>2.</b>  In the toolbar overlay at the bottom of Scene
          view, enable the <b>Cameras</b> option to get a preview of what the camera
          can see.\n\n<b>3.</b>  Move and rotate the camera and notice how the camera
          preview changes. \n\n<b>4.</b>  In the <b>Inspector</b> window, in the
          <b>Camera</b> component, use the <b>Field of View</b> slider to change
          how zoomed in the camera is. \n\nTry and get a good view of the ball bouncing
          action, but don\u2019t worry about getting the perfect angle yet \u2014
          you\u2019ll do that in the next step. "
